titles.title: The Busy Executive's Database Guide
titles.notes: An overview of available database systems with emphasis on common business applications. Illustrated.

titles.title: Cooking with Computers: Surreptitious Balance Sheets
titles.notes: Helpful hints on how to use your electronic resources to the best advantage.

titles.title: You Can Combat Computer Stress!
titles.notes: The latest medical and psychological techniques for living with the electronic office. Easy-to-understand explanations.

titles.title: Straight Talk About Computers
titles.notes: Annotated analysis of what computers can do for you: a no-hype guide for the critical user.

titles.title: Silicon Valley Gastronomic Treats
titles.notes: Favorite recipes for quick, easy, and elegant meals.

titles.title: The Gourmet Microwave
titles.notes: Traditional French gourmet recipes adapted for modern microwave cooking.

titles.title: But Is It User Friendly?
titles.notes: A survey of software for the naive user, focusing on the 'friendliness' of each.

titles.title: Secrets of Silicon Valley
titles.notes: Muckraking reporting on the world's largest computer hardware and software manufacturers.

titles.title: Computer Phobic AND Non-Phobic Individuals: Behavior Variations
titles.notes: A must for the specialist, this book examines the difference between those who hate and fear computers and those who don't.

titles.title: Is Anger the Enemy?
titles.notes: Carefully researched study of the effects of strong emotions on the body. Metabolic charts included.

titles.title: Life Without Fear
titles.notes: New exercise, meditation, and nutritional techniques that can reduce the shock of daily interactions. Popular audience. Sample menus included, exercise video available separately.

titles.title: Prolonged Data Deprivation: Four Case Studies
titles.notes: What happens when the data runs dry? Searching evaluations of information-shortage effects.

titles.title: Emotional Security: A New Algorithm
titles.notes: Protecting yourself and your loved ones from undue emotional stress in the modern world. Use of computer and nutritional aids emphasized.

titles.title: Onions, Leeks, and Garlic: Cooking Secrets of the Mediterranean
titles.notes: Profusely illustrated in color, this makes a wonderful gift book for a cuisine-oriented friend.

titles.title: Fifty Years in Buckingham Palace Kitchens
titles.notes: More anecdotes from the Queen's favorite cook describing life among English royalty. Recipes, techniques, tender vignettes.

titles.title: Sushi, Anyone?
titles.notes: Detailed instructions on how to make authentic Japanese sushi in your spare time.
